  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GFD and BSFP Borno State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due to the increasing needs in these newly accessible areas, Action Against Hunger performed a rapid assessment in Nganzai in November 2016.  The findings noted the presence of severe and moderate acute malnutrition (SAM &amp;amp; MAM) and, while there was a functioning market, the team observed that the IDPs practiced only limited petty trading and begging as a means of livelihoods.  AAH is currently delivering nutritional support for pregnant and lactating women and children under five through partnerships with UNICEF and WFP respectively and non-food items with the support of ECHO.  However, food needs remain significant for the whole population in accessible areas in Nganzai and no humanitarian actors have begun to provide food assistance in Magumeri or Kukawa.  In order to address the significant, immediate food needs in recently accessible areas, AAH is proposing to partner with WFP to deliver a general food distribution (GFD) and blanket supplementary food support (BSFP) to vulnerable households in accessible areas of Nganzai, Monguno and Kukawa LGAs.</narrative>
  </description>
